HEADWORD: Unliquidated
<hw>Un*liq"ui*da`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
liquidated; not exactly ascertained; not adjusted or settled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unliquidated damages</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>,
<cd>penalties or damages not ascertained in money.</cd>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unliquored</ent>⟦br⟧
